ENTRY            30301   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30301001   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 13         38
TITLE      Cross-sections for fast neutron induced reactions on
            85Rb, 190Os and 192Os nuclei
AUTHOR     (W.Augustyniak, J.Bielewicz, M.Herman, A.Marcinkowski)
INSTITUTE  (3POLIFJ)
REFERENCE  (P,INDC(SEC)-42,205,1974) Brief report, tables
REL-REF    (O,30350001,W.Augustyniak+,J,APP/B,7,347,1976)
            Superseded data for 85Rb(n,p)85mKr
           (O,30443001,M.Herman+,J,NP/A,297,335,1978)
            Superseded data for 190Os(n,n')190mOs
           (O,30444001,W.Augustyniak+,J,NP/A,285,145,1977)
            Superseded data for 192Os(n,3n)190mOs
EXP-YEAR   (1974)
INC-SOURCE (D-T) T(d,n) alpha reaction
SAMPLE     Natural high purity samples
METHOD     (ACTIV) The reaction final products were identified by
            their characteristic gamma-ray transitions.
DETECTOR   (GELI)30 cm3 Ge(Li) detector whose efficiency in the
            50 keV to 2 MeV energy range was determined using the
            known intensity relations of gamma-rays from 226Ra,
            133Ba and 169Yb sources
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Data errors include:
           .Statistical errors
           .Error of detection efficiency
           .Error of flux determination
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by Marcinkowski,1/12/1975.
HISTORY    (19751201R) Data also received from priv.comm.
             by Marcinkowski, 1/12/1975.
           (19750731C) CA.
           (19760414A) KO. -More data for Rb-85(n,p) at 4.1,4.3,
            13.03,15.94 and 16.60 MeV added.  'Analysis' was
            inserted in sub-entry 005 and other minor changes in
            BIB section.-
           (19760914A) Subentries .002 and .003 are superseded by
            APP/B,7(1976)347,(EXFOR 30350).
           (19780427A) KO.-Subentry .004 and .005 are superseded.-
           (20090115A) BIB section updated
           (20260407D) VT. Subents 002, 004-005 deleted
           (20260407A) VT. Revision in 003
ENDBIB              38
